==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: migr
<hw>⟦Eacute⟧`mi`gr⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., emigrant.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One of the natives of
<country>France</country> who were opposed to the first Revolution, and
who left their country in consequence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>Any emigrant, especially one
who had fled his/her native land due to political conditions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eminence</ent>⟦br⟧
